drop table "CON_Condition" cascade constraints;

/*==============================================================*/
/* Table: "CON_Condition" */
/*==============================================================*/
create table "CON_Condition"
(
"ConditionID" NUMBER(32) not null,
"ContractID" NUMBER(32) not null,
"SAPContractCode" VARCHAR2(20),
"CompanyCode" VARCHAR2(20) not null,
"EntityCode" VARCHAR2(20) not null,
"TermType" INTEGER not null,
"ConditionType" VARCHAR2(10) not null,
"CalcObjectType" VARCHAR2(10) not null,
"CalcObjectID" VARCHAR2(200) not null,
"DistObjectType" VARCHAR2(10) not null,
"DistObjectID" VARCHAR2(200) not null,
"ValidFrom" TIMESTAMP not null,
"ValidTo" TIMESTAMP not null,
"Currency" VARCHAR(10) default 'CNY' not null,
"ISOCurrency" VARCHAR(10) default 'CNY' not null,
"TermCode" VARCHAR2(10),
"FreqTermCode" VARCHAR2(10),
"UnitPrice" NUMBER(10,2) not null,
"CalcFormula" VARCHAR2(10) not null,
"CalcRulerOne" VARCHAR2(100),
"CalcRulerTwo" VARCHAR2(100),
"DistFormula" VARCHAR2(10) default 'B' not null,
"DistRulerOne" VARCHAR2(100) default 'Z010' not null,
"DistRulerTwo" VARCHAR2(100) default 'M2' not null,
"ExtPurpose" VARCHAR(10) not null,
"PostingStartDate" TIMESTAMP,
"ChangeIndicator" CHAR(1) default 'N' not null,
"SyncSAPflag" INTEGER default 0 not null,
constraint PK_CON_CONDITION primary key ("ConditionID")
);
